title._content: St. James Church in Keene New Hampshire

description._content: TITLE St. James Church in Keene New Hampshire CREATOR Wardwell, Anne, Keene NH SUBJECT Churches - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION "When St. James Church was erected, it like St. Bernard's on Main Street, the Unitarian Church on Washington Street, and the Methodist Church on Court Street, acted as the transitional building between the business section of town and the residential area. Now it is isolated from the few remaining examples of domestic architecture on the street and is surrounded by commercial construction." [Also seen on the right is the Soldiers' Monument in Central Square.] PUBLISHER Keene Public Library and the Historical Society of Cheshire County DATE DIGITAL 20090226 DATE ORIGINAL 1975 RESOURCE TYPE slides FORMAT image/jpg RESOURCE IDENTIFIER hsykfok054 RIGHTS MANAGMENT No known copyright restrictions.
